The Claude Code UI is showing a permission dialog that needs to be clicked **Allow** (your text reply doesn't satisfy it — it's a button click in the app). If you don't see it, here's the simplest path: create the file manually.

**Create this file:** `C:\Temp\theia-test2\run\.claude\settings.json`

With exactly this content:

```json
{
  "hooks": {
    "PreToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "mcp__theia__(save_artifact|commit_process_files)",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node \"C:/Temp/theia-test2/run/tools/theia-write-hook.js\""
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

You can do this in Notepad, VS Code, or any text editor — just make sure the `.claude` folder exists first (you may need to create it). Once that file exists, the hook will fire automatically on every future Theia save call and the artifact uploads will start working. Let me know when it's in place and I'll retry the save.

